[These cases were confirmed on the End Polio Pakistan website (see http://www.endpolio.com.pk/polioin-pakistan/polio-cases-district-wise-2019). Transmission of the WPV1 continues in both Pakistan and Afghanistan (a newly confirmed case was reported last week in Afghanistan). As this article clearly states, a key problem has been the growing antivaccination groups that are convincing parents not to vaccinate their children. How does one effectively deal with this? We haven't been successful in the western cultures, as seen with the ongoing measles outbreaks. A major dilemma.

The HealthMap/ProMED map of Pakistan can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6641139,140.

A good map showing the provinces and districts of Pakistan can be found at https://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/pak215_pakistan_districts_v5_a0_20181203.pdf. - Mod.MPP]
